{
  "texts": [
    "The unknowns are the weight parameters of the encoder and the decoder.",
    "Reinforcement learning (RL) is a machine learning method that seeks to learn a policy (x|) by training an agent to perform a task by interacting with its environment in discrete time steps.",
    "setting requires four components: state space, action space, state transition probabilities, and reward.",
    "The agent selects an action that is sent to the environment.",
    "A reward and a new state are sent back to the agent from its environment and used by the agent to improve its policy at the next time step."
  ]
}